________________________________________________________________________________
Which of the following statements do you think sounds better to an employer?
<ol>
 	<li>Made Excel spreadsheets</li>
 	<li>Entered data into Excel</li>
 	<li>Organized data using Excel</li>
</ol>
<strong>Tip: </strong>To make an excellent one-line statement, be sure to include a result:

<em>Organized data using Excel to improve the efficiency of the team meetings</em>

________________________________________________________________________________
Can you rewrite the following resume statements to make them concise? <em>Tip: try to eliminate words that are redundant, and focus on actions and accomplishments instead of details.</em>
<ul>
 	<li>Cross-promoted the Snowboarding Exhibition with ABCD Radio involving a sweepstakes contest for consumers, which successfully built awareness for the Snowboarding Exhibition and promoted the ABCD radio station.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li>Planned a charity event to raise money for charity which involved using networking and interpersonal skills to talk to local business owners to earn sponsorships, donations of money or gift cards that could be raffled off during the charity event for charity.</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<ul>
 	<li>I used my degree in Finance to develop marketing strategies and sales programs in support of our three major product lines, which increased profitability by 30% in the first year.</li>
</ul>
